# Control-plane paths (see policy/control-plane.yaml) — MAINTAINERS ONLY.
# Last match wins in CODEOWNERS, so these override the `*` rule above: a
# contributor's review does NOT satisfy the gate for these files; only an
# admin/maintainer code owner does. This is the SERVER-SIDE backstop for the
# A7 transport gap: a fine-grained PAT can be denied the "Workflows" permission
# so it cannot edit .github/workflows/** over https, but an SSH deploy key is
# NOT scope-limited and can. CODEOWNERS + required review closes that on merge
# to main regardless of transport. Requires branch protection with
# require_code_owner_reviews:true and required_approving_review_count>=1
# (harness-core profile already declares both; live is currently 0 — human fix).
